text:
Singer Brandy Norwood was hospitalized Friday after she lost consciousness on a plane before takeoff.

The 38-year-old star was on a Delta aircraft at Los Angeles International Airport when she passed out, prompting her to be removed from the plane, TMZ reported.

Paramedics from the Los Angeles City Fire Department arrived on the scene and began assisting her on the jetway, where she eventually regained consciousness, according to the website.

She was reportedly in stable condition when she was transported to a local hospital.

Brandy Norwood sings on NYC subway in disguise

Norwood was bound for New York's JFK Airport before the medical scare.

It's currently unclear what caused her to lose consciousness.

The singer and actress is best known for songs such as "The Boy Is Mine" and "Have You Ever," and for her starring role in the sitcom "Moesha."
